==English==

===Etymology=== 
Dates to college slang of the 1860s (originally "put on dog").

===Idiom===

'''[[put]] [[on]] the [[dog]]'''

#{{idiom}} To [[dress up]]; to [[put on airs]]; to make a [[show]] of [[wealth]] and/or [[importance]]; to be [[pretentious]]. Similar to "put on the ritz".

